snippet.title: Depp's ex wife arrives at UK court for libel trial
snippet.description:
(7 Jul 2020) Actress Amber Heard, ex-wife of actor Johnny Depp, arrived at Britain's High Court on Tuesday to attend a hearing of Depp's claim against The Sun’s publisher, News Group Newspapers over a story alleging he was abusive to her.
Depp is suing the publication, along with its executive editor, Dan Wootton, for libel over an article that branded him a “wife beater.” 
The paper ran a story in 2018 claiming Depp was violent towards Heard.
Depp strongly denies the allegations.
Depp, 57, and model-actress Heard, 34, have accused each other of acting abusively.
